// Inside top level component render
function handleToggle(calendarEvent) {

}
//grandparent (Events themselves and STATE live here)
<EventList events={this.state.events} toggleHandler={this.handleToggle.bind(this)}

will contain multiple instances of
   <SingleEvent event={event} toggleHandler={this.props.toggleHandler} >   //parent
     <TouchableHighlight onPress={this.props.toggleHandler.bind(this, event)} />  //child





___________________________
togglehandler is bound at the child level to a particular event and then the method calll is passed up to the parent which is then passed to the grand parent which changes the actual STATE of the event

State flows downward only, views are rerendered if state changes


